I am also including the tactical sling (partially seen to the left of the stock) as well as 5 - 30 round polymer magazines, 4 of which have a handy window to see how much ammo is remaining. The Kimber Model 84M is the first ultra-lightweight production rifle that combines classic design, hand finishing and the advantages of a Mauser claw extractor for true controlled round feeding and extraction. The Model 84M action was designed with minimal dimensions to accept the .308 Win. family of cartridges. No compromise was considered. Most production rifles simply shorten their bulky, full-sized actions to accommodate these shorter cartridges, and their rifles end up weighing the same as a magnum. The Kimber Model 84M Montana weighs just over 5 pounds, and the Model 84M Classic, Classic Stainless, Classic Select Grade and SuperAmerica weigh about 8 ounces more. Varmint, LongMaster Classic, Pro Varmint, SVT and LongMaster VT are available in several flat-shooting varmint calibers. All Kimber rifles feature match grade barrels with match grade chambers and target crowns for exceptional accuracy. Barrels are optimum length to maximize velocity and maintain perfect balance, not cut to save weight.
Model 84M rifles are the lightest production hunting rifles available today. The Model 84M Montana .308 Win. weighs just 5 pounds, 2 ounces. Models with walnut stocks weigh just 8 ounces more.

title: For Sale:  1884 US Trapdoor Springfield Line Throwing Gun
postcontent:
Trapdoor Springfield 1884 Line Throwing Gun With Original Case & Accessories. Very rare gun used by the U.S. Navy, Coast Guard , Merchant Marines and other organizations to throw rescue lines over the bow of disabled ships. It shoots a brass bolt attached to the rope via .45 caliber blanks.

This gun has an 1884 dated Civil War Springfield lock plate.These Springfield Line Guns were used in the Spanish American War and World War One eras and so saw some serious action. They were later decommissioned and replaced after the wars with inexpensive single barrel shotguns converted to line guns .

The fitted wood case measures 33 inches long. Included are ten brass bolts, three rope cans, all of which are full, empty box of ammo.

Because of their rarity it's a bit difficult to find comparable sales of these Trapdoor Springfield Line Guns but I was able to verify one sale for $2150.00 a few months ago. Excellent investment opportunity and a rare piece of Naval history.
